---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dylan Purbrick | Cover Letter" activeTab="cover-letter">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4">Cover Letter</h1>
        <p class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">Graduate Application Archive</p>
    </header>

    <div class="bg-white p-12 md:p-20 shadow-xl font-neue text-slate-800 leading-relaxed space-y-12">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start border-b border-slate-100 pb-8">
            <div class="space-y-1">
                <p class="font-black uppercase text-xl text-industrial-black">Dylan Purbrick</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400">Mo. 0451 317 463 | Dylan.m.purbrick@gmail.com [cite: 45, 46]</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400">Bondi, NSW 2026 [cite: 47]</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-500">10/03/2026 [cite: 48]</p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500">
            <p>Industrus Engineering [cite: 49]</p>
            <p>IndustrusEng.com.au</p>
            <p>Australia</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <p class="font-black uppercase text-industrial-black tracking-tight">RE: GRADUATE ENGINEER PROGRAM APPLICATION [cite: 50]</p>
            
            <p>Dear Hiring Manager, [cite: 51]</p>
            
            <p>
                I am writing to apply for the Graduate Engineer Program at Industrus Engineering[cite: 52]. I am currently finishing my final year of a Bachelor of Engineering (Honours) in Mechatronic Engineering at UTS while working as an Engineering Assistant at Keith Engineering[cite: 53]. My professional journey is driven by a deep passion for mechanical systems and a belief that the best learning happens through hands-on experience[cite: 54].
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-8 pl-6 border-l-2 border-slate-100">
                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Professional Accountability</h3>
                    <p>At Keith Engineering, I am often responsible for the final quality check of manufacturing drawings, ensuring every detail is technically accurate to prevent material waste[cite: 56, 57]. I systematically cross-reference CAD models against Bills of Materials (BOM) to catch discrepancies[cite: 58]. This has taught me that accountability is about ensuring the final product is safe and efficient[cite: 60].</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Technical Communication</h3>
                    <p>I act as a bridge between technical drafting teams and clients[cite: 62]. I take technical site visit reports and summarize them into clear project costs and customer quotes, translating complex data into accessible information so customers feel confident in our process [cite: 63-65].</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Innovation & Engineering Proofs</h3>
                    <p>I designed functional, print-in-place pliers using additive manufacturing, utilizing tight tolerance control in Fusion 360 [cite: 68-70]. Additionally, I developed a ROS 2 perception subsystem for an autonomous robot using OpenCV, achieving a 90% success rate during physical testing[cite: 74, 77].</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Leadership & Performance</h3>
                    <p>As a co-founder and Team Executive of the UTS MechSoc, I oversaw our executive team and organized large-scale events for 30 people[cite: 86, 87]. I successfully balanced this with my shift supervisor role and a rigorous engineering degree, demonstrating self-reliance and organization under pressure [cite: 80-83].</p>
                </section>
            </div>

            <p>I am eager to bring this collaborative mindset and my hands-on background to the teams at Industrus[cite: 90, 91].</p>

            <div class="pt-8">
                <p>Best Regards,</p>
                <p class="font-black uppercase text-xl">Dylan Purbrick [cite: 93]</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
